  "texts": [
    "Proprietary deep research systems are significantly more expensive; OpenAI Deep Research costs USD 1.80 per query on SQAv2, and Ai2 ScholarQA (using Claude Sonnet) costs USD 1.30 per query.",
    "In comparison, DR Tulu costs approximately USD 0.00008 per query, assuming the user has already paid the hardware and hosting costs (only including the cost of API calls in the query cost).",
    "foot_7 Including the LM inference cost when running DR Tulu via OpenRouter with Qwen3-8B pricing, 9 the total cost is approximately USD 0.0018 per query.",
    "This further demonstrates the strong cost-effectiveness of smaller, open-LM deep research models compared to proprietary systems, in addition to non-monetary benefits such as preserving sensitive data locally.",
    "Compared to other open deep research models, DR Tulu remains significantly cheaper despite its superior performance: Tongyi DR and Webthinker cost around USD 0.03 and USD 0.003 (for WebThinker in report mode, the cost is USD 0.015 per query) per query, respectively."
